      },
      en: {
        'nav.perfil':'Profile','nav.formacao':'Training','nav.arte':'Art',
        'nav.ensino':'Teaching','nav.imprensa':'Press','nav.presenca':'Presence',
        'nav.galeria':'Gallery','nav.entrevistas':'Interviews',
        'hero.tagline':'Marechal Deodoro · Alagoas · Brazil',
        'hero.subtitle':'Dancer · Choreographer · Teacher',
        'hero.desc':'From Alagoas, recognized as one of the pioneers of Arabic dance in Northeast Brazil. Decades dedicated to oriental art, training dancers, and preserving Egyptian culture through movement and spirituality.',
        'hero.cta':'Discover the profile','hero.badge':'Years of<br>Art','hero.scroll':'Scroll to discover',
        'sobre.title':'Pioneer of Arabic dance<br>in the <em>Northeast</em>',
        'sobre.p1':'<strong>Soraya Magalla</strong> is a dancer, choreographer, and teacher from Alagoas, recognized for her journey in Arabic dance across Brazil, especially in the Northeast. Considered by students and admirers as one of the pioneers of belly dance in the region.',
        'sobre.p2':'Over decades, she dedicated herself to <em>training dancers</em> and promoting oriental culture, teaching courses, workshops, and performances in various Brazilian cities — from Alagoas to Paraná.',
        'sobre.p3':'Her work goes beyond the stage: she researched, documented, and taught, ensuring that the cultural richness of oriental dance flourishes and evolves in the northeastern lands. A <em>guardian of an ancient tradition</em>.',
        'sobre.quote':'"Choreographer of Egyptian Ballet, Arabic Dances and Flamenco"','sobre.cite':'— Soraya Magalla, Instagram',
        'stat.career':'Years of<br>career','stat.styles':'Dance<br>styles','stat.pioneer':'Pioneer in<br>Alagoas','stat.reference':'Reference in<br>Northeast',
        'formacao.title':'A journey of<br><em>discoveries</em> and art',
        'tl.1.title':'Eliana Cavalcanti School','tl.1.desc':'Soraya began her training in classical ballet at the Eliana Cavalcanti dance school, where she developed the technical foundations of movement and awakened her passion for physical expression.',
        'tl.2.title':'Technical deepening','tl.2.desc':'She studied at CENART in Alagoas, deepening her technical and artistic knowledge — a fundamental step in building her identity as an artist.',
        'tl.3.title':'The great discovery','tl.3.desc':'During a dance cycle at Teatro Santa Isabel in Recife, she was discovered by renowned Polish choreographer Halina Biernacka — an encounter that would change the course of her career forever.',
        'tl.4.title':'Madeleine Shahrazad School','tl.4.desc':'The recognition opened doors to São Paulo, where Soraya studied at the traditional Arabic dance school Madeleine Shahrazad — consolidating her specialization in oriental art.',
        'tl.5.title':'International expansion','tl.5.desc':'After São Paulo, Soraya took dance beyond national borders, performing and studying at festivals and residencies in Greece — bringing her work closer to the international circuit.',
        'tl.6.title':'Flamenco in Madrid','tl.6.desc':'She recently studied flamenco in Madrid, further expanding her dance palette and fusing Spanish sensibility with her oriental foundation.',
        'tl.7.title':'Living legacy','tl.7.desc':'With decades of experience, Soraya returned to the Northeast to share what she learned, training generations of dancers and making Alagoas a reference point for oriental dance in Brazil.',
        'espec.title':'The <em>arts</em> that<br>define Soraya',
        'espec.intro':'More than a dancer, Soraya is a multifaceted artist. Her work blends tradition, theatre, spirituality, and technique — creating a unique and personal language.',
        'spec.1.desc':'A unique fusion between classical ballet and Egyptian dance movements. Soraya developed performances that unite the technical precision of ballet with the expressiveness and ancestry of ancient Egyptian art.',
        'spec.2.desc':'An ancient art rooted in Egypt, belly dance is at the heart of Soraya\'s work. She explores its therapeutic, spiritual, and feminine aspects, beyond the traditional technique.',
        'spec.3.desc':'Spanish passion meets the Arabic soul. Flamenco forms part of Soraya\'s artistic palette as a natural extension of her search for the most intense and dramatic physical expression.',
        'spec.4.desc':'The connection between movement and feminine spirituality. Soraya incorporates into her work a vision of dance as ritual, healing, and self-knowledge — transforming the stage into a sacred space.',
        'prof.title':'Training new<br><em>generations</em>',
        'prof.p1':'<strong>Soraya Magalla</strong> devoted a great part of her career to teaching. She became known for training new dancers and promoting Arabic culture in the Northeast.',
        'prof.p2':'She taught <em>courses, workshops, and performances</em> in different Brazilian cities, bringing oriental art wherever she went — from Alagoas to the interior of Paraná.',
        'prof.quote':'"Dance has been used as a form of therapy capable of overcoming and strengthening women\'s self-esteem, contributing to physical and emotional balance."',
        'prof.li1':'Courses and workshops in multiple Brazilian cities','prof.li2':'Training of dancers performing throughout the Northeast',
        'prof.li3':'Promotion of Arabic and oriental culture in the region','prof.li4':'Performances with a therapeutic and spiritual focus','prof.li5':'Projects linked to the sacred feminine and oriental culture',
        'imp.title':'In the Brazilian <em>media</em>','imp.intro':'From Alagoas to Paraná — five decades of journalistic coverage documenting Soraya Magalla\'s journey through the Brazilian press.',
        'pres.title':'Art beyond<br>the <em>stage</em>','pres.intro':'Soraya Magalla\'s presence goes far beyond live performances. Her art reaches people across multiple platforms and cultural contexts throughout Brazil.',
        'gal.title':'Moments in <em>motion</em>','gal.intro':'Three decades of art captured in images — from the stages of Alagoas to international scenes.',
        'ent.title':'Voice and <em>movement</em>','ent.intro':'Soraya Magalla has given interviews and participated in audiovisual productions that document her journey, her art, and her contributions to oriental culture in Brazil.',
      },
